<item>
            <title>[LU-10554] trivial typo on lnetctl command line generates LBUG on lustre client</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-10554</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m trying lnetctl commands. I tried to specify interface as ib0 and it crashed client node with LBUG.&lt;br/&gt;
I think lnetctl can just report the error without LBUG.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;root@tev0509 rpmbuild&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;# lnetctl net show&lt;br/&gt;
net:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;net type: lo&lt;br/&gt;
      local NI(s):&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;nid: 0@lo&lt;br/&gt;
          status: up&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;net type: o2ib&lt;br/&gt;
      local NI(s):&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;nid: 192.168.176.72@o2ib&lt;br/&gt;
          status: up&lt;br/&gt;
          interfaces:&lt;br/&gt;
              0: ib0&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;lnetctl lnet unconfigure&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;lnetctl lnet configure&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;lnetctl net show&lt;br/&gt;
net:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;net type: lo&lt;br/&gt;
      local NI(s):&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;nid: 0@lo&lt;br/&gt;
          status: up&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;



&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;lnetctl net add --if ib0&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Message from syslogd@tev0509 at Jan 23 15:30:15 ...&lt;br/&gt;
 kernel:LNetError: 30614:0:(api-ni.c:1499:lnet_startup_lndnet()) ASSERTION( libcfs_isknown_lnd(lnd_type) ) failed: &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Message from syslogd@tev0509 at Jan 23 15:30:15 ...&lt;br/&gt;
