                            <comment id="219521" author="sharmaso" created="Wed, 31 Jan 2018 11:01:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue is anyways resolved with &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-10151&quot; title=&quot;lnetctl gives the worst configration warning&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-10151&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-10151&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. With &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-10151&quot; title=&quot;lnetctl gives the worst configration warning&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-10151&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-10151&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, check for incomplete user data is put in place which errors out for missing information while adding NI.&#160;&lt;br/&gt;
With the above patch though, LASSERT on data from userspace is removed and the missing information is checked for and handled gracefully in kernel as well.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
